    <h1>Privacy Policy for IIPE</h1>

    <p class="last-updated">
        Last Updated: [Insert Date]
    </p>

    <p>
        Welcome to <strong>IIPE</strong> ("App", "we", "our", or "us"). We are committed to
        protecting your privacy and ensuring that your personal information is handled securely
        and responsibly.
    </p>

    <p>
        This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and protect information
        when you use the IIPE mobile application.
    </p>

    <p>
        By using the App, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance
        with this Privacy Policy.
    </p>

    <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>

    <h3>Personal Information</h3>

    <p>We may collect the following information when you register or use our services:</p>

    <ul>
        <li>Full name</li>
        <li>Email address</li>
        <li>Phone number</li>
        <li>Date of birth</li>
        <li>Address</li>
        <li>Emergency contact details</li>
        <li>User account credentials</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Health Information</h3>

    <p>
        Depending on the services provided through the App, we may collect:
    </p>

    <ul>
        <li>Medical history</li>
        <li>Consultation records</li>
        <li>Appointment details</li>
        <li>Treatment information</li>
        <li>Health assessments</li>
        <li>Notes entered by healthcare providers</li>
        <li>Uploaded medical documents or images</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Device Information</h3>

    <p>We may automatically collect:</p>

    <ul>
        <li>Device model</li>
        <li>Operating system version</li>
        <li>Application version</li>
        <li>Device identifiers</li>
        <li>IP address</li>
        <li>Crash reports and diagnostic information</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. How We Use Information</h2>

    <p>We use the collected information to:</p>

    <ul>
        <li>Provide healthcare-related services</li>
        <li>Schedule and manage appointments</li>
        <li>Maintain patient records</li>
        <li>Facilitate communication between users and healthcare providers</li>
        <li>Send reminders and notifications</li>
        <li>Improve application performance</li>
        <li>Provide customer support</li>
        <li>Comply with legal and regulatory requirements</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. Data Storage and Security</h2>

    <p>
        We take reasonable administrative, technical, and physical measures to protect your information.
    </p>

    <p>Security measures may include:</p>

    <ul>
        <li>Encrypted communication (HTTPS/TLS)</li>
        <li>Secure cloud hosting</li>
        <li>Access controls and authentication</li>
        <li>Regular security monitoring</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
        However, no method of electronic transmission or storage is completely secure,
        and we cannot guarantee absolute security.
    </p>

    <h2>4. Sharing of Information</h2>

    <p>We do not sell your personal information.</p>

    <p>We may share information with:</p>

    <h3>Healthcare Providers</h3>

    <p>
        Information may be shared with authorized healthcare professionals involved in your care.
    </p>

    <h3>Service Providers</h3>

    <p>
        We may use trusted third-party providers for:
    </p>

    <ul>
        <li>Cloud hosting</li>
        <li>Push notifications</li>
        <li>Analytics</li>
        <li>Technical support</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
        These providers are required to protect your information and use it only for authorized purposes.
    </p>

    <h3>Legal Requirements</h3>

    <p>
        We may disclose information if required by law, court order, or governmental authority.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Google Services</h2>

    <p>
        The App may use services provided by Google, including:
    </p>

    <ul>
        <li>Firebase</li>
        <li>Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM)</li>
        <li>Google Play Services</li>
        <li>Google Analytics (if enabled)</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
        These services may collect limited information as described in their respective privacy policies.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Notifications</h2>

    <p>
        The App may send notifications related to:
    </p>

    <ul>
        <li>Appointment reminders</li>
        <li>Consultation updates</li>
        <li>Health-related communications</li>
        <li>System announcements</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
        You may manage notification preferences through your device settings.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Data Retention</h2>

    <p>
        We retain personal and health information only for as long as necessary to:
    </p>

    <ul>
        <li>Provide services</li>
        <li>Maintain medical records</li>
        <li>Comply with legal obligations</li>
        <li>Resolve disputes</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
        When information is no longer required, it will be securely deleted or anonymized.
    </p>

    <h2>8. User Rights</h2>

    <p>
        Depending on applicable laws, users may have the right to:
    </p>

    <ul>
        <li>Access their personal information</li>
        <li>Correct inaccurate information</li>
        <li>Request deletion of information</li>
        <li>Withdraw consent where applicable</li>
        <li>Request a copy of their data</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
        Requests can be submitted using the contact information below.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Children's Privacy</h2>

    <p>
        The App is not intended for children under the age required by applicable law without
        parental or guardian consent.
    </p>

    <p>
        If we become aware that information has been collected from a child without appropriate
        consent, we will take steps to remove the information.
    </p>

    <h2>10. International Data Transfers</h2>

    <p>
        Your information may be stored and processed on servers located outside your country of residence.
    </p>

    <p>
        By using the App, you consent to such transfers where permitted by law.
    </p>

    <h2>11. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>

    <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time.
    </p>

    <p>
        Any changes will be posted within the App and on the Privacy Policy page.
        Continued use of the App after updates constitutes acceptance of the revised policy.
    </p>

